<subSubSection lastPageId="44" lastPageNumber="45" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1436,1999,2026]" lastBlockId="44.[151,1436,152,618]" lastPageId="44" lastPageNumber="45" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,326,1999,2025]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Observations:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boulenger" authorityYear="1902" box="[334,614,2000,2025]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tropidonotus">
<emphasis box="[334,614,2000,2025]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Liolaemus tropidonotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
represents an additional controversial species apparently related to 
<taxonomicName lastPageId="44" lastPageNumber="45" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis box="[1412,1436,2000,2025]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">L.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[151,268,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">annectens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pincheira-Donoso" authorityYear="2005" box="[332,455,152,177]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="signifer">
<emphasis box="[332,455,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">L. signifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. After its original description (
<bibRefCitation author="Boulenger" box="[836,1032,152,178]" firstAuthor="Boulenger" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="394 - 402" refId="ref52813" refString="Boulenger, G. A. (1902) Descriptions of new batrachians and reptiles from the Andes of Peru and Bolivia. Annals and Magazine of Natural History of London, 10, 394 - 402." type="journal article" year="1902">Boulenger 1902</bibRefCitation>
), 
<bibRefCitation author="Burt &amp; Burt" box="[1057,1295,152,178]" firstAuthor="Burt" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="227 - 395" refId="ref53048" refString="Burt, C. E. &amp; Burt, M. D. (1931) South American lizards in the collection of the American Museum of Natural History. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 61, 227 - 395." type="journal article" year="1931">Burt &amp; Burt (1931)</bibRefCitation>
placed this taxon into the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burt &amp; Burt" authorityYear="1931" box="[480,646,192,217]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="multiformis">
<emphasis box="[480,646,192,217]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">L. multiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(which is in turn a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Laurent 1992" authorityName="Laurent" authorityYear="1992" box="[1020,1386,192,218]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="annectens" subSpecies="fide">
<emphasis box="[1020,1219,192,217]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">L. annectens fide</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Laurent" box="[1226,1386,192,218]" firstAuthor="Laurent" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref64066" refString="Laurent, R. F. (1992) On some overlooked species of the genus Liolaemus Wiegmann (Reptilia-Tropiduridae) from Peru. Breviora, 494, 1 - 33." type="journal article" year="1992">Laurent 1992</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; see also 
<bibRefCitation author="Etheridge &amp; Espinoza" box="[205,534,232,258]" firstAuthor="Etheridge" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="1 - 64" refId="ref59521" refString="Etheridge, R &amp; Espinoza, R. E. (2000) Taxonomy of the Liolaeminae (Squamata: Iguania: Tropiduridae) and a semiannotated bibliography. Smithsonian Herpetological Information Service, 126, 1 - 64." type="journal article" year="2000">Etheridge &amp; Espinoza 2000</bibRefCitation>
). However, in a recent taxonomic reassessment, 
<bibRefCitation author="Nunez, H." box="[1101,1262,232,258]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="28 - 34" refId="ref67402" refString="Nunez, H. (2004) Cambios taxonomicos para la herpetofauna de Argentina, Bolivia y Chile. Noticiario Mensual Museo Nacional de Historia Natural de Chile, 353, 28 - 34." type="journal article" year="2004">Núñez (2004)</bibRefCitation>
suggested that the 
<typeStatus box="[196,246,272,298]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">type</typeStatus>
series of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boulenger" authorityYear="1902" box="[366,548,272,297]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tropidonotus">
<emphasis box="[366,548,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">L. tropidonotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(preserved in the British Museum of Natural History of London) exhibits substantial patterns of morphological differentiation from the group of Andean species consisting of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boulenger" authorityYear="1901" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="annectens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">L. annectens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pincheira-Donoso &amp; Nunez" authorityYear="2005" box="[284,440,352,377]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pleopholis">
<emphasis box="[284,440,352,377]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">L. pleopholis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pincheira-Donoso" authorityYear="2005" box="[500,623,352,377]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="signifer">
<emphasis box="[500,623,352,377]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">L. signifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Cei" box="[689,801,352,378]" firstAuthor="Cei" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" refId="ref54875" refString="Cei, J. M. (1993) Reptiles del noroeste, nordeste y este de la Argentina. Herpetofauna de las selvas subtropicales, Puna y Pampas. Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali di Torino, Monografie 14, 949 pp." type="book" year="1993">Cei 1993</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pincheira-Donoso &amp; Nunez" box="[815,1216,352,378]" firstAuthor="Pincheira-Donoso" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" refId="ref69923" refString="Pincheira-Donoso, D. &amp; Nunez, H. (2005) Las especies chilenas del genero Liolaemus (Iguania, Tropiduridae, Liolaeminae). Taxonomia, sistematica y evolucion, Publicacion Ocasional del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural de Chile, Santiago, 486 pp." type="book" year="2005">Pincheira-Donoso &amp; Núñez 2005</bibRefCitation>
). This author concluded that the distinctive traits observed among these taxa do not support the idea of their synonymy, and that therefore, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boulenger" authorityYear="1902" box="[273,455,432,457]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tropidonotus">
<emphasis box="[273,455,432,457]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">L. tropidonotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be revalidated, at least while a more detailed evaluation provides contrary evidence. Since no other study has so far been presented, we follow 
<bibRefCitation author="Nunez, H." box="[954,1135,472,498]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="28 - 34" refId="ref67402" refString="Nunez, H. (2004) Cambios taxonomicos para la herpetofauna de Argentina, Bolivia y Chile. Noticiario Mensual Museo Nacional de Historia Natural de Chile, 353, 28 - 34." type="journal article" year="2004">Núñez’s (2004)</bibRefCitation>
criteria, and recognize 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boulenger" authorityYear="1902" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tropidonotus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">L. tropidonotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a species different from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boulenger" authorityYear="1901" box="[642,793,512,537]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="annectens">
<emphasis box="[642,793,512,537]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">L. annectens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pincheira-Donoso" authorityYear="2005" box="[856,978,512,537]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="signifer">
<emphasis box="[856,978,512,537]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">L. signifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We believe that these morphological contrasts (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Nunez, H." box="[320,467,552,578]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="28 - 34" refId="ref67402" refString="Nunez, H. (2004) Cambios taxonomicos para la herpetofauna de Argentina, Bolivia y Chile. Noticiario Mensual Museo Nacional de Historia Natural de Chile, 353, 28 - 34." type="journal article" year="2004">Núñez 2004</bibRefCitation>
, for details) may be the result of independent adaptive radiations leading to fully segregated phylogenetic lines.
</paragraph>
